list.item:
The circumstances under which a Sessional
                     Lecturer appointment is appropriate are normally limited to the following: 

to replace a Member who is on leave or on
                           another assignment of duties; 

when the search for an individual with
                           the required qualifications for an advertised continuing position is
                           unsuccessful; 

when the appointment is for a pilot
                           project of limited duration; 

when unanticipated enrolment increases
                           makes such an appointment necessary in the short term; 

to integrate members of a professional
                           community into the University’s teaching program; 

or when a person with the required
                           qualifications fills a limited on-going pedagogical need of a Department,
                           Faculty/School curriculum.

The only disciplinary measures which may be taken by the Board against a Sessional Lecturer are the following:
a letter of reprimand or censure may be placed in the Personal File of the Sessional Lecturer;
the Sessional Lecturer may be dismissed for cause, in which case cause shall mean professional incompetence and/or gross misconduct and/or serious and persistent neglect of duty.
